## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-102">System.Speech の既定のセマンティック形式は W3C に準拠している[音声認識 (SISR) バージョン 1.0 のセマンティクス解釈](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765)ここの形式`tag`スクリプトが含まれる要素は`semantics/1.0`します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-102">The default semantic format for System.Speech conforms to the W3C [Semantic Interpretation for Speech Recognition (SISR) Version 1.0](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765), where the format for `tag` elements that contain script is `semantics/1.0`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-103">スクリプトを指定する必要があります<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>オブジェクトをこの形式を使用します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-103">You must specify the script for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects using this format.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-104">構文で`semantics/1.0`:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-104">In the syntax of `semantics/1.0`:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-105">ルール変数の親の rule 要素は、"out"によって識別されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-105">The Rule Variable of the containing rule element is identified by "out".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-106">ルール要素を含むルール要素の外側のルール変数へのアクセス権を持つオブジェクトの名前は、「ルール」によって識別されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-106">The name of the object that has access to the Rule Variable of rule elements outside the containing rule element is identified by "rules".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-107">最新参照されているルールから、発話に一致する結果は、"rules.latest()"で表すことができます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-107">The result from the latest referenced rule that matches the utterance can be represented by "rules.latest()".</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-108">関連付けることができますもセマンティック値、文法におけるフレーズ スクリプトを使用することがなくを使用して、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag>オブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-108">You can also associate a semantic value with a phrase in a grammar without using script, using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> object.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-109">次の例では、フライトの都市を選択するための文法を作成します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-109">The following example creates a grammar for choosing the cities for a flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-110">この例では<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>都市ごとに、都市の空港のコードにセマンティックの値を割り当てます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-110">The example uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a semantic value to each city, which is the code for the city's airport.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-111">また、例では<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>によって行われた 2 つの参照ごとに個別のセマンティック キーを割り当てるには、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>という名前のオブジェクト`cityRef`を<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>という名前のオブジェクト`cities`です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-111">The example also uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a separate semantic key for each of the two references made by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object named `cityRef` to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `cities`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-112">セマンティック キーでは、出発都市や、航空券の到着市区町村として認識されている、市区町村を識別します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-112">The semantic keys identify a recognized city as the departure city or the arrival city for the flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-113">ハンドラーを<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized>イベントでは、キーを使用して認識結果からセマンティクスを取得します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-113">The handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> event uses the keys to retrieve the semantics from the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-114">コード例では、"out"を指すルール変数を含むの<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-114">In the code example, "out" refers to the Rule Variable of the containing <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-115">式"はタイムアウトします。LeavingFrom"という名前のプロパティを指す`LeavingFrom`という名前のルールのルール、Variable の`bookFlight`します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-115">The expression "out.LeavingFrom" refers to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-116">式"rules.flightCities"が参照するルールのルール変数が<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A>は`flightCities`ルールの参照の対象であるとします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-116">The expression "rules.flightCities" refers to the Rule Variable on the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities`, and which is the target of a rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-117">例では、式"はタイムアウトします。LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"ルールから値を割り当てますが<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A>は`flightCities`という名前のプロパティを`LeavingFrom`という名前のルールのルール、Variable の`bookFlight`します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-117">In the example, the expression "out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;" assigns the value from the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities` to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-118">参照してください[セマンティック結果コンテンツ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe)、[文法ルール名を参照する](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9)、および[文法ルールの参照が参照する](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e)詳細についてはします。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-118">See [Semantic Results Content](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe), [Grammar Rule Name Referencing](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9), and [Grammar Rule Reference Referencing](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e) for more information.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize a SpeechRecognitionEngine object.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Create a rule for the cities, assign a semantic value to each city.  
        SrgsRule cities = new SrgsRule("flightCities");  
        SrgsItem chi = new SrgsItem("Chicago");  
        chi.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"ORD\";"));  
        SrgsItem bos = new SrgsItem("Boston");  
        bos.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"BOS\";"));  
        SrgsItem mia = new SrgsItem("Miami");  
        mia.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"MIA\";"));  
        SrgsItem dal = new SrgsItem("Dallas");  
        dal.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"DFW\";"));  
  
        SrgsOneOf airports = new SrgsOneOf(chi, bos, mia, dal);  
        cities.Add(airports);  
        cities.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Private;  
  
        // Create a rule reference to the rule for cities.  
        SrgsRuleRef cityRef = new SrgsRuleRef(cities);  
  
        // Create the root rule for the grammar.  
        SrgsRule bookFlight = new SrgsRule("flightBooker");  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("I want to fly from"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("to"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
        // Initialize the SrgsDocument, set the root rule, add rules to the collection.  
        SrgsDocument itinerary = new SrgsDocument(bookFlight);  
        itinerary.Rules.Add(cities);  
  
        // Create a Grammar object and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar g = new Grammar(itinerary);  
        g.Name = ("City Chooser");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(g);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.                  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Write to the console the text and the semantics from the recognition result.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Speech recognized: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Semantic results:");  
      Console.WriteLine("  The departure city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["LeavingFrom"].Value);  
      Console.WriteLine("  The arrival city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["GoingTo"].Value);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1a36a-119">上記の例のコードで生成された文法の XML 形式を次に示します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1a36a-119">The following is the XML form of the grammar generated by the code in the example above.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>  
<grammar xml:lang="en-US" root="flightBooker" tag-format="semantics/1.0"   
version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar">  
  
  <rule id="flightBooker" scope="public">  
    <item> I want to fly from </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
    <item> to </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
  </rule>  
  
  <rule id="flightCities" scope="private">  
    <one-of>  
      <item> Chicago <tag> out="ORD"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Boston <tag> out="BOS"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Miami <tag> out="MIA"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Dallas <tag> out="DFW"; </tag></item>  
    </one-of>  
  </rule>  
  
</grammar>  
```
